          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The internet has proven time and time again that it is one of the most powerful tools we have access to. It certainly came in handy when trying to locate a ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ferrari F40",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/research/1991-ferrari-f40/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that was previously owned by the son of infamous leader Sadam Hussein. People everywhere took to their computers and browsers and became internet investigators as if they were on the hunt for gold. While it seems like this story should be more of a movie plot than real life, this all happened thanks to a YouTube channel by Ratarossa.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/05/ferrari-f40.jpg",
        "cardWidth": "wide",
        "alt": "<img src=\"ferrari-f40.jpg\" alt=\"A Ferrari \">"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A video was posted to the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ratarossa YouTube channel",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCA0ZY1x5r2lyKQfoUYvHvqQ",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " asking for help to locate a particular famous abandoned vehicle with incredible value. Even another YouTube channel Solomondrin threw the idea out to 1.6 million followers to help find the car along with a $1,000 reward. That's when the internet detectives went to work, and soon enough, leads started pouring in with information regarding the car, the condition, and possible locations. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Once the car was located, the pictures started flooding in, and it was obvious that the car was in bad shape with sand covering its neglected body and engine, and even the interior was worse for wear. The pictures would make any car enthusiast cringe for any car in this condition, but even more so on an expensive ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ferrari",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/handpicked/ferrari-812-superfast-is-offered-from-the-halo-car-collection/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " F40, a car that could easily fetch over $1 million. To add insult to injury, this car only has over 3,000 kilometers (1,864 miles) on the odometer meaning that this Ferrari is basically brand new and hasn't even been fully broken in yet. It almost appears as if somebody deliberately trashed it.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Like many cases big or small, most information brought forward is likely thrown out, but the best leads were provided by Chris at Gas Monkey Garage. These guys were known for taking a demolished Ferrari F40, flipping it, and selling it for copious amounts of cash.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Back in 2016, Chris actually tried to buy the exact car in question after a call from Richard Rawlings, and he even went as far as to travel to Iraq to find it. Interestingly enough, he did find the car, but due to the logistics along with security worries, the transaction became null. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=10&v=sePEm1XYnG0&feature=emb_logo",
        "html": "<iframe width=\"612\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/sePEm1XYnG0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>",
        "metadata": {
          "author_name": "Ratarossa",
          "title": "Abandoned Ferrari F40 Treasure Hunt - Gas Monkey Garage & Salomondrin Step In To Help The Search",
          "version": "1.0",
          "thumbnail_width": 480,
          "author_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCA0ZY1x5r2lyKQfoUYvHvqQ",
          "height": 344,
          "provider_url": "https://www.youtube.com/",
          "thumbnail_height": 360,
          "thumbnail_url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sePEm1XYnG0/hqdefault.jpg",
          "width": 612,
          "provider_name": "YouTube"
        },
        "embedType": "video"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "After Chris's attempt, a ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ferrari",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/bagged-ferrari/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " restoration expert from Belgium also made the trip to Iraq to see how he could help the F40. In fact, he was able to get the car back to decent shape, but that proved to be no easy task. The engine needed to be stripped down to bare bones and completely rebuilt. Also, another ECU was needed for the car, so it was sourced and then remotely programmed for the twin-turbo V8. While this wasn't easy, it was doable. In fact, the F40 was spotted driving down the road just last year by the same Ferrari mechanic.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "So, where is the car now? After it was brought back to road-worthy condition, a wealthy Saudi man purchased the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ferrari ",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/handpicked/1982-ferrari-magnum-pi/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "for his collection, and had it shipped over to be restored. Some viewers were able to catch up with the man and see how the F40 was fairing, and there are some videos of him driving it along his property. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
